Alhaji Alhassan Adamu, the Emir of Kajuru, has regained his freedom. The monarch, who was abducted by bandits alongside 13 others, was freed on Monday. Channels TV reports that the Sarkin Kajuru was released around the forest areas leading to Kajuru castle. It was also learnt that the other 13 persons abducted from the monarchâ€™s private residence are still in captivity. As at time of filing this report, it is unclear if any ransom was paid.